eed 3.5<b>. <strong> Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add to bowl with almond mixture and stir together well. Transfer mixture to a piping bag fitted with a plain nozzle (approx. 5 mm) then pipe 3 cm rounds onto prepared trays. Tap trays 3-4 times on work surface to remove any air bubbles then bake for 15 minutes (120°C)."},{"content":"Remove from oven and immediately transfer silicone baking mats to work surface to stop the cooking. Allow to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes) before gently peeling macarons off mats. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and nozzle then prepare filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"White Chocolate Buttercream Filling"},{"content":"Place chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt <b>2 min\/40°C\/speed 0.5<b>."},{"content":"Add icing sugar and butter then mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a plain nozzle (approx. 5 mm)."},{"content":"Pipe buttercream on flat side of half the macarons, then sandwich with other halves."},{"content":"Decorate as desired (see tip) and serve, or store in an airtight container in fridge for up to 3 days."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use shop bought egg whites if preferred; two large egg whites weigh approx. 70 g.","Decorate with a white chocolate drizzle: place 30 g white chocolate, in small pieces or callets, in mixing bowl then melt <strong>1.5 min\/50°C\/speed <\/strong>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt again <strong>30 sec\/50°C\/speed <\/strong>. Transfer to a small piping bag fitted with a 1-2 mm plain nozzle then pipe over tops of macarons.","Use other colours of food colouring for different coloured macarons.","Raspberry jam, white chocolate ganache or whipped cream would also make good fillings instead of buttercream."],"basicInfo":["advanced","25m","1h 30m","30 pieces"]}